    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>'You Don't Have To Take the Bait'</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Elizabeth Lancaster letter calls Robert Mackey's May 21 Lives column on undercover investigator India absurd</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Robert Mackey's Lives column (May 21) was the most absurd thing you've published in many years. If India is an undercover investigator, what are you doing publishing her photograph as well as her alias? The whole thing reads like the plot of a lowbrow television movie.</p>
        <p>Elizabeth Lancaster</p>
        <p>Amherst, Mass.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
